Since you’re on Arch with Hyprland and Neovim, you have the perfect "Triumvirate" of tools to build a zero-latency, zero-cost AI workflow.

To avoid the "per-token bullshit" while having quick access, here are the three best ways to integrate Gemini/Claude without leaving your flow.

1. The Neovim Popup (Best for Contextual Coding)
If you just want to ask a question about the code you're looking at without opening a full sidebar like Avante, use CodeCompanion.nvim.

The Workflow: Highlight code (or not) and hit a keybind to open a small, floating prompt.

Why it's better than the web: It automatically pulls in the current buffer context so you don't have to copy-paste.

The Setup: Use the Gemini API key (Free Tier).

Lua
-- Example mapping for a quick floating chat
vim.api.nvim_set_keymap("n", "<leader>aq", "<cmd>CodeCompanionChat Toggle<cr>", { noremap = true, silent = true })
2. The Terminal Popup (Best for General Logic/Shell)
Since you’re on Arch, you should leverage the official Claude Code or Gemini CLI. These are terminal-native and feel incredibly "Unix-y."

Claude Code: npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code. It's an agentic CLI that can run commands, search your files, and answer questions.

The "Neovim" integration: You don't even need a plugin. Just use :term claude inside a Neovim split.

The Advantage: It’s faster than any GUI. You type claude "how do I fix this systemd error?", it answers, and you hit Ctrl-D to get back to work.

3. The Hyprland "Scratchpad" (The Productivity Cheat Code)
This is the "pro" move. Instead of tying the AI to Neovim, tie it to a global Hyprland keybind. This way, you can ask questions while looking at your browser, a terminal, or your config files.

Tool: Use Pyprland or a standard Hyprland scratchpad.

The Setup:

Create a "Special Workspace" (scratchpad) for a terminal running gemini or claude.

Bind it to Mod + Space.

Hyprland Config Example:

Bash
# hyprland.conf
bind = $mainMod, Space, exec, pypr toggle ai_chat
(In your pyprland.json, define ai_chat as a kitty terminal running gemini-cli.)

