Feature	Neovim Popup (CodeCompanion)	Terminal CLI (Gemini CLI)	Hyprland Scratchpad
Best For	"Explain this function"	"Write a quick bash script"	"I'm stuck on a system error"
Context	Full access to your code buffers	Access to local files	Global (visible over any app)
Cost	Free (Gemini AI Studio Key)	Free (Gemini) / Sub (Claude)	Free (Gemini AI Studio Key)
Vibe	Integrated & Seamless	Fast & Functional	Instant & Everywhere
My Recommendation: 1.  For Neovim: Set up CodeCompanion with a Gemini API key. Use it for inline "What does this do?" questions.
2.  For Global: Set up a Hyprland Scratchpad running the Gemini CLI. It feels like having a "God Mode" terminal that slides down from the top of your screen whenever you're confused, then disappears when you're done.

